quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  40,50,"They (keepers) will say: “Did there not come to you Messengers with clear evidences? They will say: “Yes.” They will reply: “Then pray (as you like)!” But the invocation of the disbelievers is nothing but in error"
  40,51,"Surely, We will make Our Messengers victorious and those who believe in worldly life and on the Day when the witnesses will stand"
  40,52,The Day when their excuses will not benefit the wrongdoers. The curse will be for them and for them will be evil abode (painful punishment)
  40,53,"And indeed We gave Moses the guidance, and We caused the children of Israel to inherit the Scripture (the Torah)"
  40,54,a guide and a reminder for people of understanding
  40,55,"So be patient (O Muhammad). Surely, the Promise of Allah is true, ask forgiveness for your fault, and glorify the praises of your Lord in the early evening Hours and in the early morning Hours"
  40,56,"Surely, those who dispute about Allah’s Verses without any authority bestowed to them, there is nothing else in their hearts except arrogance. They will never have it (Prophethood which Allah has bestowed upon you). So seek refuge with Allah. Surely, He is the All-Hearer, All-Seer"
  40,57,"The creation of the heavens and the earth is indeed a greater task than the creation of mankind, yet most of mankind does not know"
  40,58,"And not equal are the blind and those who see; nor are equal those who believe and do righteous deeds, and those who do evil. Little do you think"